  <p>  There&#39;s just one more transformation to make, and that is the perspective projection. It is finally time to convert our 3D points into 2D points, but we need to make sure that the camera&#39;s perspective is taken into account. But what does that perspective actually mean for our image?</p>
  <p>  Let&#39;s look at the camera&#39;s field of view. These dashed lines represent the boundaries of what the camera can see, and I&#39;ve highlighted a certain chunk of the camera&#39;s view for us to look at. You can see it sort of looks like a pyramid with the top chopped off - this shape is called a <em>frustum</em>. Also notice in this picture that we have drawn a couple squares on each end of the frustum, both the same size.</p>

